brewery.brewery_name: Garden Grove Brewing and Urban Winery
brewery.brewery_description: Garden Grove Brewing & Urban Winery is on a mission to channel our immeasurable creativity into extraordinary beer and wine. Even as the target moves with every new batch, our foundation is rooted in balance, passion and sustainability. This informs our business, guides our brewing and wine making and reflects who we are at the core.

brewery.brewery_name: Garden Grove Brewing and Urban Winery

beer.beer_description: A uniquely made Belgian Abbey. Fermented with Saison yeast but rich dark malts and Yirgacheffe coffee from Rostovs Coffee & Tea make this abbey a beautiful red color, almost caramel. Yiracheffe is an Ethiopian grown bean and is Rostovs lightest roast. It has surprising aromas of citrus fruit, brambles, and wine. A healthy dose of Thompson raisins and fermented and aged in Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon barrels for one month lend a complex dark fruit and rich wine flavor. The mouthfeel and after taste are wonderfully enhanced by barrel, raisin, coffee, and wine based tannins. There is still plenty of bright fruit and pleasant acidity that balances nicely with the roast and toffee notes.

beer.beer_description: An IPA that is all American.  America is a melting pot of different cultures that express themselves in a unique way that can only be described as American. This IPA starts with classic British malts that provide a malty and toasty backbone that provides a wonderful springboard for the American IPA hops that are in style today. This IPA is bitter but with a sweet maltiness that supports the intense citrus, tropical, pine, and fruit character of the American hops.
